          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Use a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uifontmetrics"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object to support scalable custom fonts in your app. You create a font metrics object that specifies the font style—for example, body or title—that you want to use in your app. You then pass your custom font to the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uifontmetrics/2877385-scaledfontforfont"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method (or one of the other methods of this class) to obtain a font object that is based on your custom font, has the appropriate style information, and automatically scales to match the current Dynamic Type settings. "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
